@NODE Preface_eng "WatchFile - introduction"
@NEXT Guidance_eng
@PREV Overview_eng

  ================
    Introduction
  ================

  "@{B}WatchFile@{UB}" is a tool to observe the contents of a file.
  The program runs in the background and outputs a checksum
  at an interval you have to enter. If the file is changed
  while "@{B}WatchFile@{UB}" is active, you will notice that the
  checksum changes, too

  English text by Sascha Reichert,
  putzi@nightbbs.insider.org.

  Additional thanks to ...
  Hans-Werner Schober
  for his helpful support and the process-routine.

  System-requirements, AmigaOS 2.0 (V36) and better.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Guidance_eng "How to use WatchFile"
@NEXT Versions_eng
@PREV Preface_eng

  ==============
    How to use
  ==============

  @{B}WatchFile@{UB}
  ---------
  Format     @{B}WatchFile@{UB} <file> [<delay>] [OUTPUT
             <outputfile>]
  Template   FILE/A,DELAY/N,OUTPUT/K
  Path       C:

  Enter the name of the file to watch over first.

  The interval between the checksum calculations can be
  changed (default: 50=one second) by entering a value
  which will be devided by 50.
  Interval = (value / 50) of a second.

  Viewing the checksum
  Enter a filename after OUTPUT if you want to create
  a logfile or enter "PRT:" for output via printer or
  "CON:" for an output-window.

  To quit "@{B}WatchFile@{UB}", press CTRL+C.

  @{I}@{U}Example,@{UU}@{UI}  @{B}WatchFile@{UB} testfile.txt 250 @{B}OUTPUT@{UB} "PRT:"

            Calculates a checksum of "textfile.txt"
            every five seconds and outputs it via
            "PRT:" to our printer.
@ENDNODE

